      "span_text": "If one merely tests memory for the inference, failure to remember could be attributed to not storing the information or to storing and then forgetting it; if the inference is remembered, it could be because it was stored and then retrieved, or it may have been generated at the time of test without having been stored. developed a paradigm not subject to the ambiguities of interpretation of the more simple design discussed above."
